ospective investors at the time. However, some prospective backers said the=
y balked at the terms, given concerns about Twitter=E2=80=99s financial per=
formance. The Musk team didn=E2=80=99t specify a funding amount or purpose =
for the fundraise in the email.
Fidelity, one of the co-investors that backed Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s takeover o=
f Twitter, has written down its stake in Twitter by 56%, public filings sho=
w, suggesting Mr. Musk would face an uphill battle raising funds at the ori=
ginal valuation from outside investors.

If he gets $6 billion in orders for a $3 billion financing round at the ori=
ginal takeover price =E2=80=A6=C2=A0I don=E2=80=99t even know what to say. =
That would be amazing. He also testified that he has raised =E2=80=9Cmore m=
oney than anyone in history by a significant margin,=E2=80=9D so he=E2=80=
=99s good at raising money and has devoted fans, but even for him this seem=
s like a heavy lift.

